President Biden has announced the appointment of several individuals to key roles in the National Quantum Initiative Advisory Committee and the U.S. Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board. The National Quantum Initiative Advisory Committee is responsible for providing an independent assessment of the National Quantum Initiative Program and making recommendations for its improvement. The committee consists of leaders from industry, academia, and federal laboratories. The U.S. Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board is an independent federal agency that performs technical and scientific peer reviews of the Department of Energy's activities related to managing and disposing of high-level radioactive waste and spent nuclear fuel. The board reports its findings and recommendations to Congress and the Secretary of Energy.